redshift. Treating quasar clustering as a bivariate function of both
redshift and luminosity, we find no evidence for luminosity dependence
in quasar clustering, and that redshift evolution thus affects quasar
clustering more than changes in quasars' luminosity. Our results are
robust against a range of systematic uncertainties. We provide a new
method for quantifying stellar contamination in photometrically
classified quasar catalogs via the correlation function.},
